## Intent

AI Session Summarizer adds an on-demand, AI-generated summary to every Claude Code session in Swob. Instead of relying on the raw `firstUserMessage` (which is often a vague continuation prompt), the summarizer reads the session's key turns and produces a 2–3 sentence digest: what was being built, what decisions were made, and what the outcome was.

**Why this matters for Swob users.** Power users accumulate hundreds of sessions. "Fix the bug" or "Continue from where you left off" tells you nothing three weeks later. A crisp AI summary — generated once and cached — makes sessions instantly recognizable in the sidebar and searchable by outcome rather than just keyword.

**Design principles.**
- **Lazy, cached generation**: summaries are produced on first view and stored in the Library's session metadata. Re-opening the same session is instant.
- **Non-blocking**: summary generation happens in a background IPC call after the session detail panel renders. The UI never waits.
- **Graceful degradation**: if `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is absent or the API call fails, the component hides itself entirely — no error toast, no broken panel.
- **Privacy-preserving**: only the first 10 user turns and last 5 assistant turns are sent for summarization, never tool results or file contents. Users can opt-out per-session via a toggle in the info panel.

**What gets added to Swob.**

1. **`summarizer-backend`** — hooks into `session.parse.post_build` to attach a `summaryStatus: 'pending' | 'ready' | 'error'` field to SessionSummary. Registers a new IPC handler `summary:generate` that accepts a sessionId and streams the Claude API response, then saves the result to the Library's session metadata via `config:setSessionMeta`.

2. **`summarizer-toolbar-btn`** (optional) — injects a ✦ button into `toolbar.actions`. Clicking it triggers `summary:generate` for the currently selected session and scrolls the info panel to the summary section.

3. **`summarizer-info-panel`** (optional) — injects a collapsible "AI Summary" section at the top of `info_panel.sections`, above the existing metadata rows. Shows a skeleton while generating, the summary text once ready, and a ↺ regenerate button.

```yaml probes:
- id: probe-session-summary-entity
  target: entity
  surface: SessionSummary
  description: "Verify SessionSummary entity exists with firstUserMessage and filePath fields — minimum required to generate a meaningful summary."
  check:
    type: entity_fields
    entity: SessionSummary
    required_fields:
      - name: firstUserMessage
        types: [string]
      - name: filePath
        types: [string]
      - name: sessionId
        types: [string]
  on_fail: abort
  message: "SessionSummary entity not found or missing required fields. Cannot generate summaries without session data."

- id: probe-session-hook
  target: hook
  surface: session
  description: "Verify session.parse.post_build hook exists to attach summary status to freshly parsed sessions."
  check:
    type: hook_exists
    hook: session.parse.post_build
    hook_signature:
      receives: [summary, filePath]
      can_augment_return: true
  on_fail: abort
  message: "session.parse.post_build hook is absent. The summarizer backend cannot attach to the session loading pipeline."

- id: probe-toolbar-slot
  target: slot
  surface: toolbar
  description: "Verify toolbar.actions slot exists to inject the summarize button."
  check:
    type: slot_exists
    slot: toolbar.actions
    accepts: [react_element]
  on_fail: warn
  message: "toolbar.actions slot not found — summarizer-toolbar-btn will be skipped. AI Summary panel in InfoPanel still works."

- id: probe-info-panel-slot
  target: slot
  surface: info_panel
  description: "Verify info_panel.sections slot exists to inject the AI Summary section."
  check:
    type: slot_exists
    slot: info_panel.sections
    accepts: [react_element]
  on_fail: warn
  message: "info_panel.sections slot not found — summarizer-info-panel will be skipped. The toolbar button will still trigger generation but results won't be displayed inline."
```

```yaml ncv:
- id: no-full-content-sent
  constraint: "The summarizer MUST NOT send tool_result content, file contents, or base64 image data to the Claude API. Only textContent fields from user and assistant turns are permitted."
  enforcement: static_analysis
  patterns:
    - language: typescript
      forbidden_patterns:
        - "toolCalls"          # tool results must be stripped before API call
        - "images"             # image data must never be sent
        - "base64"
  severity: critical

- id: no-summary-overwrites-user-data
  constraint: "The generated summary MUST be stored under a dedicated key (e.g. meta.aiSummary) in sessionMeta. It MUST NOT overwrite customTitle, notes, or highlights set by the user."
  enforcement: contract
  check:
    api_call: config:setSessionMeta
    allowed_keys: [aiSummary, summaryGeneratedAt, summaryOptOut]
    forbidden_keys: [customTitle, notes, highlights]
  severity: high

- id: api-key-never-logged
  constraint: "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY MUST NOT appear in any log output, IPC payload, or error message."
  enforcement: static_analysis
  patterns:
    - language: any
      forbidden_patterns:
        - "process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY"   # must only be read, never serialized
        - "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY"
      allowed_contexts:
        - "new Anthropic({"                  # only in SDK initialization
  severity: critical
```

```yaml contracts:
- id: contract-summary-generate-success
  description: "Requesting a summary for a valid session returns a 2–3 sentence digest within 10 seconds and stores it in sessionMeta."
  given:
    session_exists: true
    session_has_messages: true
    anthropic_api_key: present
  when:
    action: ipc summary:generate
    args:
      sessionId: "test-session-id"
  then:
    - response.status: ok
    - response.summary: length_between(80, 400)
    - db.sessionMeta[test-session-id].aiSummary: equals(response.summary)
    - db.sessionMeta[test-session-id].summaryGeneratedAt: present
    - db.sessionMeta[test-session-id].customTitle: unchanged

- id: contract-summary-graceful-degradation
  description: "If ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is absent, the IPC handler returns status:'skipped' and no sessionMeta is written."
  given:
    session_exists: true
    anthropic_api_key: absent
  when:
    action: ipc summary:generate
    args:
      sessionId: "test-session-id"
  then:
    - response.status: skipped
    - response.reason: "no_api_key"
    - db.sessionMeta[test-session-id].aiSummary: absent

- id: contract-opt-out-respected
  description: "If the user has set summaryOptOut:true for a session, summary:generate returns status:'opted_out' without calling the API."
  given:
    session_exists: true
    sessionMeta[test-session-id].summaryOptOut: true
    anthropic_api_key: present
  when:
    action: ipc summary:generate
    args:
      sessionId: "test-session-id"
  then:
    - response.status: opted_out
    - anthropic_api: not_called
```
